    "liquidRingCompressors.workingPrinciple.subtitle":
      "Liquid Ring Compressors",
    "liquidRingCompressors.workingPrinciple.mainDescription":
      "In a liquid ring compressor, the casing is partially filled with sealing liquid. As the impeller rotates, the liquid is centrifuged outward to form a stable liquid ring along the casing wall. Because the impeller is mounted eccentrically, variable compression chambers are created between its blades. Process gas enters through the conical distributor with two suction and two discharge ports. During each revolution, gas is drawn into the suction chambers, compressed as the chamber volume decreases, and then discharged through the outlet ports. This cycle occurs twice per revolution, providing continuous compression.",
    "liquidRingCompressors.workingPrinciple.step1.title":
      "Smooth, vibration-free operation",
    "liquidRingCompressors.workingPrinciple.step2.title":
      "sealing liquid circulation and control systems",
    "liquidRingCompressors.workingPrinciple.step3.title":
      "deliver safe, reliable, and oil-free performance",

    "liquidRingCompressors.models.title": "Available Models:",
    "liquidRingCompressors.models.subtitle":
      "Explore our range of claw vacuum pumps and their performance.",

    "liquidRingCompressors.benefits.title": "Benefits & Advantages",
    "liquidRingCompressors.benefits.toughGases.title": "Handles tough gases",
    "liquidRingCompressors.benefits.toughGases.description":
      "Liquid ring design safely handles saturated, corrosive, or contaminated gas streams without sacrificing performance or compressor life.",
    "liquidRingCompressors.benefits.nonContact.title": "Non-contact internals",
    "liquidRingCompressors.benefits.nonContact.description":
      "No internal contact between components minimizes wear and reduces heat, vibration, noise, and maintenance.",
    "liquidRingCompressors.benefits.continuousCooling.title":
      "Continuous liquid cooling",
    "liquidRingCompressors.benefits.continuousCooling.description":
      "Cool service liquid removes compression heat and keeps a thermally stable condition for safe compression of hazardous, explosive, or thermally sensitive gases.",
    "liquidRingCompressors.benefits.nearIsothermal.title": "Near-isothermal",
    "liquidRingCompressors.benefits.nearIsothermal.description":
      "Isothermal-like compression helps the compressor run cooler and maximizes the service life of bearings and seals.",

